The paper proposes a novel architecture for a neural associative memory, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). The architecture is based on the visual cortex of macaque brain, which suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the performance of the network in eliminating noise, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper presents computational experiments, which could fall under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) or control systems (cs.SY).
